cs.IR, cs.DS, cs.LG, cs.SI, cs.CE 

This paper deals with the problem of content ranking in a social news website, which involves optimizing multiple metrics simultaneously and satisfying traffic requirements. This problem is related to information retrieval (cs.IR), as it involves ranking content based on user behavior. It also involves optimization (cs.DS) and machine learning (cs.LG) techniques to solve the multi-objective problem. The use of genetic algorithms and performance evaluation metrics suggests a focus on computational engineering (cs.CE) and statistical learning (cs.SI).
